{
  "name": "courtyard",
  "description": "Fingerstyle nylon guitar warming a sunlit Spanish courtyard, gentle and intimate. Soft plucked nylon strings with warm woody body resonance and gentle fingertip noise: a round low bass string grounds the courtyard, a soft singing lead fingerpicks the melody while a brighter higher string weaves a counter-line above, a muted thumb-plucked tone fills the sweet woody middle, a flute-pure natural harmonic chimes, tiny string-flicks sparkle with light delay echoes, a strummed chord blooms into a lush room wash, a rolled fingerstyle arpeggio cascades, a soft body-tap keeps the dry percussive pulse, and a bright harmonic flick adds a tender little Spanish accent. A major @ A=432, additive and warm, classical and Mediterranean, never dark or harsh.",
